The paper deals with a learning variant of the cascade model for ranking web pages, which involves identifying the most attractive items from a list of K web pages. This problem is related to learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). The paper proposes two algorithms for solving the problem and derives upper and lower bounds on the regret. These topics are closely related to the subcategories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely subcategories for this paper.
